			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Been reading this kind of posts for ages on this board now, our main problem seems to actually be the huge difference in play style. Some mages want to solo, i my self stopped soloing at level 55 and havent looked back since, and therefor want it all, slow, snare 1meg hp pets and so on. And im sure the issues decribed in this, and many other posts, are quite true.
<br />

<br />
I am a high end raiding mage and for me mana is never a problem, ei dont need pet canni, i have 6k+ mana, and when a fight is over, normally, im still at 50% mana, why? easy, aggro, i cant chain nuke a lot, ill out aggro a 72 people raid with no problem at all if i do.
<br />
The issues for me is that pet doesnt last very long on raids due to huge AEs, sure PoC helps a lot on DD AE mobs, but many of em have DoT AEs, and PoC dont help much there.
<br />
Another issue is, pre time, fire based nukes, in PoFire all mobs ar 100% fire resistant, and have high magic resist, so my best nuke and my magikot gloves are of no use, and PoFire is probably the best zone for farming EP-questarmor drops. So it hurts my ego a bit not to be able to use my prime nuke so to speak. Same goes for Sol Ro Tower of course, 100% FR. 
<br />

<br />
Both issues are very real i think, but how are we gonna come to a consensus on what mages need when the playstyles are so different between the soloing mage and the raiding mage? 
<br />
The problem have no solution that i can see, we are just to different within the community, maybe give raiding mages what they need as effects on the armor we get in high end zones? but then again, i would do much better than the no high end raiding mage when i exp in lower zones thus making it unfair to mages that are not in uber guilds.
<br />

<br />
Maybe the problem is that mages is so damn god soloers at lower levels that when we get high enough we are too used to solo and therefor not wanting to group, i dont know.
<br />
Because we are so different in style and aim for playing EQ we will never agree enough to make a list of things SoE need to fix that all mages can be happy with, and then SoE will do as they please, as they have done up til now.
<br />

<br />
Sorry, i just cant see any way to make us agree to this, wich about 1000000 posts here clearly shows.
<br />

<br />
/Zandrama</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
