				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I fully agree with the origional posters views.  Very accurate about his wants for the mage class and requests of how to improve it.  I think just about everyone wants a fire pet that they can summon permarooted like SoR and will not stand their trying to buff itself long after you have given it the order to attack.  I am unsure as to whether a larger mana pool or much better mana regen is the answer to it's nuking problems though.  Take away it's roots, AoE's and dispells already though, this is a pet, not a NPC and should not use the same logic coding as to what it should deside to cast.
<br />

<br />
Although it would be nice to toss in cold nukes to the mix of fire and magic, somehow I don't see them breaking the chain of fire and magic nukes only.  I would at least be happy with the resist checks to the rains being lowered a bit, as most PoP mobs that don't have extremely low FR will usually resist 1 or 2 of the 3 waves completely making them next to useless.  I haven't had terrible issues with SV or BS on most exp mobs unless they weren't debufed at all, PoP gods are a different story though depending on the mob.
<br />

<br />
And last, but not least, pets.  I think the biggest problem with this issue is just as addressed, no statement of what mage surviveability is supposed to be in concerns to soloing in PoP.  While mages effectively have the toughest summoned pets, considering they are the only source of mob control to a soloing mage, it should be declared that either pets are at leas in consideration for being tuned, or whether some other control options(root, slow, snare) might possibly be considered if pet changes are not an option. 
