			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">On the subject of magic nukes and resistance to them, just what is a "magic nuke"?  Think of the things that currently check against MR:
<br />

<br />
Malise line
<br />
Slows
<br />
Roots
<br />
Stuns
<br />
Lightning-type DD, AoE and rains
<br />
Mezz, charm
<br />
Mana taps
<br />
Our non-fire nuke, DoT and rain lines (Black Steel, Rain of Swords, etc)
<br />

<br />
MR is a catchall for anything that doesn't fit into DR, PR, CR or FR.  One of these (at least) is not like the others - the mage magic DD line.  These are all described as summoning short-lived pointy objects to mangle a foe (cleave with a great obsidian blade, etc).  I'd think a good idea would be some way to make the resistance check for that line of spells somehow tie in to the target's AC.  If that's too much work maybe they could just be given an across-the-board resist modifier, something small even, like -30 or something.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
